## Step 5: Perform the integration.
$\int_0^{0.4} 60 (y^3 - 2y^4 + y^5) d y = 60 \left[ \frac{y^4}{4} - \frac{2y^5}{5} + \frac{y^6}{6} \right]_0^{0.4}$.

