The probability of drawing a red ball from the first urn is $8 / (8 + 7) = 8 / 15$. The probability of drawing a red ball from the second urn is $r / (r + 9)$, where $r$ is the number of red balls in the second urn. So, the probability of drawing two red balls is $(8 / 15) * (r / (r + 9))$.

