Using a standard normal distribution table, $P(Z \leq 0.50) \approx 0.6915$ and $P(Z \leq -1.50) \approx 0.0668$. Thus, $P(-1.50 \leq Z \leq 0.50) = P(Z \leq 0.50) - P(Z \leq -1.50) \approx 0.6915 - 0.0668 = 0.6247$.

## Step 6: Round the result to a reasonable number of significant figures
